{{Infobox organization |name = Akademi Kernewek |image = |size = |formation = 2015 |headquarters = [[Truro]], [[Cornwall]] |website = http://akademikernewek.org.uk/ }} '''Akademi Kernewek''' (Cornish language academy) is the official academic body responsible for the linguistic development of the [[Cornish language]]<ref name="Akademi Cornwall Council">{{cite web|title=Akademi Kernewek|url=http://www.magakernow.org.uk/leisure-and-culture/the-cornish-language/cornish-language/akademi-kernewek/|website=Maga Kernow|publisher=Cornwall Council|accessdate=26 October 2017}}</ref> It is responsible for setting standards for the language, developing dictionaries in the [[Standard Written Form]], advising on street and place names, developing terminology and carrying out research. The academy consists of a management board and four panels.<ref name="Akademi Kernewek">{{cite web|title=Akademi Kernewek|url=http://akademikernewek.org.uk/|website=Akademi Kernewek|publisher=Akademi Kernewek|accessdate=26 October 2017}}</ref>
